SIMPLE: stroking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stroking
<hw>Strok"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of rubbing gently with the hand, or of smoothing; a stroke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I doubt not with one gentle <qex>stroking</qex> to wipe away ten
thousand tears.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Needlework)</fld> <def>The act of laying small
gathers in cloth in regular order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>See <er>Stripping</er>, 2.</def>
<rj><au>Smollett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stroll</ent>⟦br⟧
